<subSubSection id="F0DE654CFF9B673400A42604FC6FFA35" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="type_taxon">
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF9B673400A42604FCEFFCE6" blockId="47.[151,925,800,855]" box="[151,834,831,855]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673400A42604FE80FCE6" bold="true" box="[151,301,831,855]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<typeStatus id="677F8865FF9B673400A42604FF62FCE6" box="[151,207,831,855]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B67340100267BFC93FCE6" authority="Foldi &amp; Kozar 2007: 59" authorityName="Foldi &amp; Kozar" authorityPageNumber="59" authorityYear="2007" box="[307,830,832,855]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paranaensis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B67340100267BFD99FCE6" box="[307,564,832,855]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Eriococcus paranaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF9B67340208267BFC93FCE6" author="Foldi, I. &amp; Kozar, F." box="[571,830,832,855]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="51 - 64" refId="ref49039" refString="Foldi, I. &amp; Kozar, F. (2007) New species and new records of Eriococcus (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) from South America. Zootaxa, 1573, 51 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">Foldi &amp; Kozár 2007: 59</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF9B673400A426BEFECBFAEE" blockId="47.[151,1436,901,2010]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673400A426BEFD89FC2E" bold="true" box="[151,548,901,927]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Generic diagnosis. Adult female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="20FF2A42FF9B6734020726BEFD21FC2E" box="[564,652,901,927]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="48.[151,257,1936,1960]" captionTargetBox="[295,1311,525,1892]" captionTargetId="figure-176@48.[273,1313,505,1914]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 22. Hempelicoccus paranaensis (Foldi &amp; Kozár). Adult female, where A = dorsal spinose seta; B = dorsal microtubular duct; D = dorsal macrotubular ducts; L = ventral loculate pore; U = cruciform pore, V = antenna; W = claw of metathoracic leg, and X = coxa of metathoracic leg (modified after Kozár &amp; Konczné Benedicty, 2008)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5313401" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5313401/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B6734029326BEFCABFC2F" box="[672,774,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Dorsum.</emphasis>
Setae spine-like, present throughout but variable in size. Macrotubular ducts long and narrow, inner ductule with flower-like glandular end. Microtubular ducts long, with oval or bifurcate orifice, either few or forming groups. Loculate pores absent. Anal lobes well developed and sclerotised. Median plate not developed. Anal ring well developed, sclerotised, with 4 pairs of setae, each twice as long as width of anal ring; anal ring pores few. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B6734036F2121FC12FB82" box="[860,959,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Margin.</emphasis>
Often clearly demarcated by a line of enlarged spinose setae. 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B67340181217BFDABFBE8" box="[434,518,1088,1113]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Venter.</emphasis>
Setae mainly hairlike and quite long but with a few spinose setae, similar to those on dorsum, present around margin. Macrotubular ducts present, of various sizes. Microtubular ducts absent. Loculate pores generally with 5 loculi but pores with more loculi common; frequent throughout. Cruciform pores present submarginally. Antennae 7 segmented. Frontal lobes present, antennal tubercles absent. Labium 3 segmented with 2 pairs of setae. Legs long, tibia and tarsus subequal in length; coxae of meso- and metathoracic legs with spinulae; metacoxae and femur with many large, irregularly-shaped translucent pores. Vulva present between segments VII and VIII. (Modified after Kozár &amp; Konczné Benedicty, 2008).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF9B673400F52051FC6FFA35" blockId="47.[151,1436,901,2010]" box="[198,962,1386,1412]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Currently known from 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673401E62051FDF4FA35" box="[469,601,1386,1412]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673402562051FD7FFA35" box="[613,722,1386,1412]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673403392051FC10FA35" authorityName="Kuprianova" authorityYear="1962" box="[778,957,1386,1412]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nothofagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Nothofagaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F0DE654CFF9B672B00F520B4FF51FE06" lastPageId="48" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF9B673400F520B4FACEF965" blockId="47.[151,1436,901,2010]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673400F520B4FEE4FA18" bold="true" box="[198,329,1423,1449]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Comment.</emphasis>
According to Kozár &amp; Konczné Benedicty (2008), 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B6734038F20ABFBC2FA18" box="[956,1135,1424,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B6734038F20ABFBC2FA18" box="[956,1135,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Hempelicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673404C420ABFAD6FA18" authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" box="[1271,1403,1424,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673404C420ABFAD6FA18" box="[1271,1403,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Eriococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having: (i) spine-like setae on the dorsum; (ii) long microtubular ducts with a bifurcate orifice; and (iii) frontal lobes; but it differs in lacking: (i) enlarged tubular ducts; and in having: (ii) 2 pairs of setae on the basal labial segment; (iii) cruciform pores; and (iv) groups of microtubular ducts on the dorsum. It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673400A4231EFEE5F98F" box="[151,328,1573,1598]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Acanthococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673400A4231EFEE5F98F" box="[151,328,1573,1598]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Acanthococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having: (i) 2 pairs of setae on the basal labial segment; (ii) cruciform pores; and (iii) frontal lobes. However it differs from 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B6734023A2370FD11F9D5" box="[521,700,1611,1636]" class="Florideophyceae" family="Cystocloniaceae" genus="Acanthococcus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gigartinales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B6734023A2370FD11F9D5" box="[521,700,1611,1636]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Acanthococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having groups of microtubular ducts on the dorsum and in lacking a median plate. It is also close to 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673402B7234BFCA1F938" box="[644,780,1648,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Coxicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673402B7234BFCA1F938" box="[644,780,1648,1673]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Coxicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having: (i) enlarged spine-like setae on dorsum; and (ii) long microtubular ducts with a bifurcate orifice, but differs in having: (i) frontal lobes; (ii) 2 pairs of setae on the basal labial segment; and (iii) absence of clavate setae ventrally on posterior abdominal segments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF9B672B00F523DBFEC2FEDD" blockId="47.[151,1436,901,2010]" lastBlockId="48.[151,1436,152,439]" lastPageId="48" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Kozár &amp; Konczné Benedicty (2008) included 4 species in this genus, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B6734041E23DBFAC3F94B" authority="(Cockerell)" baseAuthorityName="Cockerell" box="[1069,1390,1760,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B6734041E23DBFB76F948" box="[1069,1243,1760,1785]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. brasiliensis</emphasis>
(Cockerell)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673405B323DBFE64F8AE" authority="(Morrison)" baseAuthorityName="Morrison" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leguminicola">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673405B323DBFE9AF8AF" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. leguminicola</emphasis>
(Morrison)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673401E4223EFCA4F8AE" authority="(Morrison)" baseAuthorityName="Morrison" box="[471,777,1797,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mendozae">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673401E4223EFDDAF8AF" box="[471,631,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. mendozae</emphasis>
(Morrison)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B6734037F223EFB73F8AE" authority="(Foldi &amp; Kozar)" baseAuthorityName="Foldi &amp; Kozar" box="[844,1246,1797,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paranaensis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B6734037F223EFBAAF8AF" box="[844,1031,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. paranaensis</emphasis>
(Foldi &amp; Kozár)
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673405B1223EFE9BF8F5" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Miller" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Gonzalez &amp; Granara de Willink" baseAuthorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santiaguensis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673405B1223EFE9BF8F5" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">E. santiaguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B6734015C2210FD9BF8F5" box="[367,566,1835,1860]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B6734015C2210FD9FF8F5" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Miller" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Gonzalez &amp; Granara de Willink" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[367,562,1835,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tucumanensis">E. tucumanensis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
described in 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673402E72210FCF8F8F5" authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" box="[724,853,1835,1860]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673402E72210FCF8F8F5" box="[724,853,1835,1860]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Eriococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF9B673403B32211FAE7F8F5" author="Gonzalez" box="[896,1354,1834,1860]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="115 - 134" refId="ref49159" refString="Gonzalez. P. (2009) Eriococcidos (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) encontrados en Larrea spp. (Zygophyllaceae) en Argentina. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 68, 115 - 134." type="journal article" year="2009">González &amp; Granara de Willink (2009)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673405B02210FEAFF8D8" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Miller" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson &amp; Miller" baseAuthorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumiliae">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673405B02210FEAFF8D8" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">E. pumiliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described in 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B67340187226BFD93F8D8" authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" box="[436,574,1872,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B67340187226BFD93F8D8" box="[436,574,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Eriococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by P. 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF9B673402BE226BFCC1F8DB" author="Gonzalez" box="[653,876,1872,1898]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="50 - 56" refId="ref49077" refString="Gonzalez. P. (2008 a) Two new species of Eriococcus (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) from the Andino Patagonica region of Argentina, with a key to the Eriococcus species of that region. Zootaxa, 1899, 50 - 56." type="journal article" year="2008">González (2008a)</bibRefCitation>
, are here transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B673404A4226BFAFFF8D8" box="[1175,1362,1872,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673404A4226BFAFFF8D8" box="[1175,1362,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Hempelicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B6734054D226BFD65F83E" authority="(Gonzalez &amp; Granara de Willink)" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Miller" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Gonzalez &amp; Granara de Willink" baseAuthorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="santiaguensis" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B6734054D226BFE9AF83F" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. santiaguensis</emphasis>
(González &amp; Granara de Willink)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673402FC224EFC95F83E" bold="true" box="[719,824,1909,1935]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="918357AEFF9B673402FC224EFC95F83E" box="[719,824,1909,1935]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B67340374224EFA31F83E" authority="(Gonzalez &amp; Granara de Willink)" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Miller" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Gonzalez &amp; Granara de Willink" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[839,1436,1909,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tucumanensis" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B67340374224EFBA7F83F" box="[839,1034,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. tucumanensis</emphasis>
(González &amp; Granara de Willink)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B673400A422A1FEA7F805" bold="true" box="[151,266,1946,1972]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="918357AEFF9B673400A422A1FEA7F805" box="[151,266,1946,1972]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF9B6734017822A0FDD8F805" authority="(Gonzalez)" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Miller" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Hodgson &amp; Miller" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[331,629,1946,1972]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumiliae" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B6734017822A0FE72F805" box="[331,479,1947,1972]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">H. pumiliae</emphasis>
(González)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF9B6734024C22A1FD54F805" bold="true" box="[639,761,1946,1972]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="918357AEFF9B6734024C22A1FD59F805" box="[639,756,1946,1972]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
because they possess the dorsosubmedial clusters of microtubular ducts typical of this genus. It should be noted that 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF9B6734034722FBFA92F86B" author="Gonzalez" box="[884,1343,1984,2010]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="115 - 134" refId="ref49159" refString="Gonzalez. P. (2009) Eriococcidos (Hemiptera: Coccoidea) encontrados en Larrea spp. (Zygophyllaceae) en Argentina. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 68, 115 - 134." type="journal article" year="2009">González &amp; Granara de Willink (2009)</bibRefCitation>
dispute the validity of 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF84672B017425A3FE55FF00" box="[327,504,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF84672B017425A3FE55FF00" box="[327,504,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Hempelicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of variation found in all of the diagnostic characters listed by Kozár &amp; Konczné Benedicty (2008) except for the presence of clusters of dorsal microducts. Hopefully a detailed phylogenetic analysis using morphological and molecular characters of taxa currently placed in the 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF84672B053525D9FA31FF4D" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1899" box="[1286,1436,226,252]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Eriococcidae</taxonomicName>
will clarify the position of many of the currently controversial groupings. As presently understood, 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF84672B00A42416FEEAFEF7" box="[151,327,301,326]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF84672B00A42416FEEAFEF7" box="[151,327,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Hempelicoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to South America. For a description of the adult female of the 
<typeStatus id="677F8865FF84672B04A82416FB60FEF6" box="[1179,1229,301,327]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
species, see 
<bibRefCitation id="DC554B36FF84672B056C2416FEC7FEDD" author="Foldi, I. &amp; Kozar, F." pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="51 - 64" refId="ref49039" refString="Foldi, I. &amp; Kozar, F. (2007) New species and new records of Eriococcus (Hemiptera: Coccoidea: Eriococcidae) from South America. Zootaxa, 1573, 51 - 64." type="journal article" year="2007">Foldi &amp; Kozár 2007: 59</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B87B36C7FF84672B00F5244CFF51FE06" blockId="48.[151,1436,152,439]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF84672B00F5244CFE1DFE20" bold="true" box="[198,432,375,401]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">First-instar nymph</emphasis>
(based on 
<taxonomicName id="7FC44D44FF84672B021D2443FB2DFE23" authority="(Gonzalez &amp; Granara de Willink)" authorityName="Hodgson &amp; Miller" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Gonzalez &amp; Granara de Willink" baseAuthorityYear="2010" box="[558,1152,376,402]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Hempelicoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tucumanensis">
<emphasis id="8AB0EAD5FF84672B021D2443FD40FE20" box="[558,749,376,401]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">E. tucumanensis</emphasis>
(González &amp; Granara de Willink)
</taxonomicName>
; gender not determined) (
<figureCitation id="20FF2A42FF84672B00AC24A6FF5EFE06" box="[159,243,413,439]" captionStart="FIGURE 23" captionStartId="49.[151,255,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[331,1255,201,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-65@49.[306,1281,182,1928]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURE 23. Hempelicoccus paranaensis (Foldi &amp; Kozár). First-instar nymph, where A = dorsal spinose setae; B = dorsal microtubular duct; J1 = small ventral seta; J2 = large ventral setae, and L = ventral triloculate pore (redrawn and modified after González &amp; Granara de Willink, 2009)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5313405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5313405/files/figure.png" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
)
